From 2a8b877dd7b2bd39596cefe9fd841ab62e748464 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 20:45:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] init: skip securebits lock for androidd service
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

OHOS init's KeepCapability() sets SECBIT_KEEP_CAPS_LOCKED on every
service.  This is permanent — the linux capabilities(7) "locked"
bits cannot be unset.  When that bit is inherited by a service that
in turn fork+execs another init binary (e.g. Halium 12's android
init via androidd in the hybris_generic native-boot path), that
inner init can no longer toggle SECBIT_KEEP_CAPS for its own child
services that declare a `capabilities` directive — kernel returns
EPERM on PR_SET_SECUREBITS, init's pre-exec setup fails, and the
service exits with WEXITSTATUS=6.

Fix: name-check "androidd" in KeepCapability() and skip the
PR_SET_SECUREBITS call entirely for that service.  This leaves
androidd's securebits at 0, so when Halium init forks logd / netd /
etc. it can set its own KEEP_CAPS|KEEP_CAPS_LOCKED dance freely.

Verified on Volla X23 via a static aarch64 probe binary
(`logd_probe.c`) that simulates Halium init's pre-exec setup:
pre-fix PR_GET_SECUREBITS=0x20 → PR_SET_SECUREBITS(0x30) rc=-1
post-fix PR_GET_SECUREBITS=0x0  → PR_SET_SECUREBITS(0x30) rc=0.

Full root-cause writeup in
device/board/oniro/docs/hybris_generic/native_boot_plan/phase_n4_androidd.md
"2026-05-14 PM" section.

Change-Id: I8fa0949cfdce009345c224a03c2eabe07e43dded
Signed-off-by: Francesco Pham <francesco.pham1@h-partners.com>
---
 services/init/adapter/init_adapter.c | 13 +++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/services/init/adapter/init_adapter.c b/services/init/adapter/init_adapter.c
index f086b7ab..c90ad255 100644
--- a/services/init/adapter/init_adapter.c
+++ b/services/init/adapter/init_adapter.c
@@ -16,6 +16,7 @@
 
 #include <errno.h>
 #include <semaphore.h>
+#include <string.h>
 #include <sys/prctl.h>
 #include <unistd.h>
 #if defined OHOS_LITE && !defined __LINUX__
@@ -39,6 +40,18 @@ int KeepCapability(const Service *service)
         return 0;
 #else
 #ifndef OHOS_LITE
+    /* Native-boot bring-up (hybris_generic): services that fork+exec a
+     * foreign init (Halium 12's android-style init via androidd) must
+     * leave securebits unlocked so the inner init can run its own
+     * PR_SET_KEEPCAPS / PR_SET_SECUREBITS dance for its child services
+     * (logd, netd, …).  Without this skip, SECBIT_KEEP_CAPS_LOCKED would
+     * be set on androidd, causing every Halium HAL service that has a
+     * `capabilities` directive to fail PR_SET_SECUREBITS with EPERM and
+     * exit with status 6 in init's pre-exec setup. */
+    if (service != NULL && service->name != NULL &&
+        strcmp(service->name, "androidd") == 0) {
+        return 0;
+    }
     if (service->attribute & SERVICE_ATTR_SETUID) {
         if (prctl(PR_SET_SECUREBITS, SECBIT_NO_SETUID_FIXUP | SECBIT_NO_SETUID_FIXUP_LOCKED)) {
             INIT_LOGE("prctl PR_SET_SECUREBITS failed: %d", errno);
-- 
